<p>&#8216;Paul Newman KC has written a summary of the FTT decision in Morgan Lloyd Trustees Limited &#038; ors v HMRC (31 March 2023). The case concerns the appropriate approach to the valuation of intellectual property rights (including domain names), and will be bad news for trustees hoping to rely on eyebrow-raising expert valuations to escape scheme sanction charges.&#8217;</p>
